CatDescriptText: Related image published in advertisement in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 14, 1957, pg. 14, with text: "Having a wonderful time?  Said Jana.  And of course the couple said, 'Yes!'  At Jana's everything is done to increase your pleasure.  Chef Squair prepares steaks, chops, spaghetti to suit your taste.  There's music night Wednesday through Saturday.  The Eddie Russ Quartet takes the stand this week... 1250 Penna. Ave., Northside."
TitMainTitle: Two women, possibly including Jana on left, and man dining, with piano and bass player in background, Jana's club, 1250 Pennsylvania Avenue, Northside
